        <h1 itemprop="name">BrowserSync extremely slow on OS X?</h1>
        <p>If you&#39;re developing on OS X and experiencing BrowserSync to be very slow there’s a good chance that changing the .local domain in your url to .dev will fix the problem. Why? I have no idea. The fix is really illogical but hey, it works! It might have something to do with Bonjour using the .local domain as well.</p>

<p>In my case I changed <code>http://wordpress.local:8080</code> to <code>http://wordpress.dev:8080</code> et voil&agrave;, everything’s snappy again.</p>

        <footer><p>Published: <data itemprop="datePublished" value="2015-08-14">August 14, 2015</data>.</p></footer>
